this seems like simply extension of WriteFile method, if you add merge flag to it, and remove io.Writer
I would change WriteFile(path string) signature to 
WriteFile(path, options WriteOptions)
// with WriteOptions:
type WriteOptions struct {
    Merge bool
}

can u move this part to a separate function? mergedBytes(path string) error. than code would look like this:
func (k *kubeConfig) WriteFile(path string, options WriteOptions) error {
	var data []byte
	var err error

	if options.Merge && path != "" {
		data, err = k.mergedBytes(path)
	} else {
		data, err = k.bytes()
	}
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}

	return k.fileSystem.WriteFile(path, data)
}

Also this approach would allow to test mergedBytes function better, because right now I dont see much tests for it.

